Hey John,<br><br>
I appreciate your concern about the topic of flag desecration.  You certainly are allowed to express your opinions on this site, and I respect your right to speak against this particular amendment.<br><br>
This site, on which you have posted 3 longs messages, is mainly for people who are seeking solutions and common ground concerning the war in Vietnam. The topic is Vietnam, in otherwords.<br><br>
I am growing  weary of your passing judgment on our government institutions and the people who comprise them who ,by the way, were democratically elected.<br><br>
When you talk about congressional &quot;prostitutes&quot; or a &quot;Whorehouse of Representatives&quot; who are in favor of this amendment; and when you refer to other supporters of a flag desecration amendment as being ignorant, bigotted, intolerant, and infinitely corrupted, I suspect that you have a hidden agenda.<br><br>
No, I am not a right wing, conservative, flag waver. <br><br>
We heard your opinions and we have noted the url. Thank you.<br>

